But how does it work?

  • Find a solution to a cryptographic puzzle

  • Given a string \(\alpha\), find a nonce s.t. Sha-256(\(\alpha\) + nonce) < threshold

  • Nonce = ânumber only used onceâ

  • Sha-256 hashing algorithm:
    • Deterministic
    • Irreversible
    • Probabilistically unique
    • 2^256

Cryptographical puzzle

But how does it work?

  • Find a solution to a cryptographic puzzle

  • Given a string \(\alpha\), find a string nonce s.t. Sha-256(\(\alpha\) + nonce) < threshold

  • Difficulty level can be controlled with the difficulty threshold.

  • Bitcoin protocol sets the threshold s.t. a new block can be find in \(\approx\) 10 minutes

  • This process is called mining, and the finder of a new block is rewarded with coin
